  section.sg-sect#flex-grid
    h2 The Flex Grid
    p.
      A Flex Grid is simply a list of items arranged like blocks in a grid.
      It has the structure of a list in that all items share the same container
      (unlike tables where items are in different rows), while at the same time
      appearing like a table with rows and columns.
    p.
      The Flex Grid can be flexible and responsive, adjusting the number of
      columns based on screen size.
      By default, each item has full width.
      #[mark Remember to set the widths of each item in order to achieve a grid-like appearance.]
    p.
      The container must have the #[code .o-GridFlex] class and
      each item must have the #[code .o-GridFlex__Item] class.
      To remove normal list styles (padding, bullets, etc.),
      add class #[code .o-ListBare] to the container.
      If the items are normally inline elements, remember to add class
      #[code .o-Block] to each one.
